  "prompt": "How can I stop being addicted to the internet?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to help reduce internet addiction:\n\n1. Set clear boundaries\n- Establish specific times for internet use\n- Use website blockers or apps that limit screen time\n- Keep devices out of the bedroom\n\n2. Find alternative activities\n- Exercise\n- Read books\n- Pursue hobbies\n- Spend time with friends and family in person\n- Practice mindfulness or meditation\n\n3. Practice digital detox\n- Take regular breaks from devices\n- Have designated technology-free days\n- Turn off notifications\n\n4. Identify triggers\n- Understand what drives your internet use\n- Address underlying emotional needs\n- Consider counseling if addiction is severe\n\n5. Gradually reduce usage\n- Start with small, achievable goals\n- Track your progress\n- Reward yourself for meeting milestones\n\n6. Create a structured daily routine\n- Plan activities in advance\n- Schedule specific times for internet use\n- Stay physically active\n\n7. Improve self-discipline\n- Practice willpower\n- Use productivity techniques\n- Set realistic goals\n\n8. Seek support\n- Talk to friends and family\n- Join support groups\n- Consider professional help if needed\n\nRemember, change takes time and patience. Be kind to yourself throughout the process.",
